        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('System 6'); ?>
        <p><strong>System 6</strong> (also referred to as <strong>System Software 6</strong>) is a graphical user interface based operating system for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Macintosh', 'ITH'); ?> computers. It was released in 1988 by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple Computer', 'C'); ?> and was part of the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mac OS', 'OS'); ?> line of operating systems. System 6 was shipped with various Macintosh computers until it was succeeded by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('System 7', 'MAC'); ?> in 1991. The boxed version of System 6 cost $49 when introduced. System 6 is classed as a monolithic operating system. It featured an improved MultiFinder, which allowed for co-operative multitasking.</p>
